  "doc_id": "34432",
  "text": "As with previous studies, we did not find a significant association between the BMI and the maximal CSA of the IPFP [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . However, the BMI cannot discriminate adipose from non-adipose tissue. To our knowledge, no previous study has examined the association between body composition and the size of the IPFP. In this study we found that fat-free mass but not fat mass was associated with a larger IPFP. The lack of association between measures of adiposity and the size of the IPFP might suggest that the IPFP size is not simply reflected by systemic obesity. Nevertheless, the association between increased fat-free mass and a larger IPFP suggests that the size of the IPFP may be potentially modifiable by factors such as exercise.",
